cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.SD

This paper is about detecting unknown intent in dialogue systems using pre-trained deep neural network classifiers. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with natural language processing and computational linguistics. The paper also involves deep learning techniques, which makes cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) likely categories as well. Additionally, the paper uses calibration and novelty detection algorithms, which are related to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.SD (Software Engineering) respectively.
